          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two different targets of natural isotopic composition",
                "were used for proton cross section measurements. Sample",
                "no.1 comprising thin TiN and Au layers on Si substrate",
                "was prepared by TiN deposition (reactive magnetron",
                "sputtering in Ar + N2 atmosphere) and subsequent vacuum",
                "evaporation of thin gold layer which serves as an",
                "internal standard. The former technique was employed",
                "also for the preparation of sample no.2 comprising TiN",
                "layer on Be backing. Both samples were thoroughly",
                "investigated by the standard RBS method using 2 MeV",
                "alpha particles to determine their composition and",
                "thickness. The measured relative areal densities",
                "of relevant elements irt sample no.1 were",
                "N:Ti:Au = (9.5 :to.5): (8.4 :to.5): 1 and in",
                "sample no.2 Ti:N = (0.98 :t 0.05): 1. The measured",
                "thickness of TiN layers (in TiNlcm-2)on sample no. 1",
                "and no. 2 was 3.8 x 1017 and 6.0 x 1017, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
